# Metagenomic Analysis and Functional Inference of Gut Microbiota in Drosophila melanogaster

## Project Overview

This project was conducted as part of my M.Sc. Genetics thesis.

The objective was to analyze publicly available whole genome sequencing (WGS) datasets to characterize the gut-associated microbiota of Drosophila melanogaster and identify dominant microbial metabolic pathways.

## Tools Used

- Linux
- FASTQC
- KneadData
- Kraken2
- HUMAnN
- Galaxy

## Workflow

Raw WGS Data
↓
FASTQC
↓
KneadData
↓
Kraken2
↓
HUMAnN
↓
Taxonomic and Functional Analysis

## Key Activities

- Quality assessment of sequencing reads
